Statement.paragraph:
Currently 653 miles of the nearly 2,000 miles of the Southern 
Border is fenced at a cost of nearly $7 billion since fiscal year 2007. 
This fencing consists of:
  &lt;bullet&gt; 353 miles of primary fencing;
  &lt;bullet&gt; 300 miles of vehicle fencing;;
  &lt;bullet&gt; 36 miles of secondary fencing behind the primary fencing;
  &lt;bullet&gt; 14 miles of tertiary fencing behind the secondary fence.

In order to achieve the long-term goal of securing the proper 
staffing at CBP to address workloads, NTEU recommends that Congress 
take the following actions:
  &lt;bullet&gt; Fill 1,200 CBP officer current vacancies;
  &lt;bullet&gt; Fund the additional 2,500 CBP officer needed new hires;
  &lt;bullet&gt; Address the polygraph process to mitigate excessive (60

percent) applicant polygraph failures;
  &lt;bullet&gt; Fund 721 CBP agriculture specialists needed new hires;
  &lt;bullet&gt; Restore recruitment and retention awards, and other
